        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 9 at 9:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 915 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Haswell, or 35 miles north of North La Junta, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Haswell.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM MDT for
southeastern Colorado.</instruction>
